Definition: patronymically from {{h3458}}; a Jishmaelite or descendant of Jishmael; Ishmaelite.
from {{h8085}} and {{h410}}; God will hear; Jishmael, the name of Abraham's oldest son, and of five Israelites; Ishmael.
from {{h3486}}; an old man; (very) aged (man), ancient, very old.
from {{h3456}}; a desolation; desert, Jeshimon, solitary, wilderness.
from {{h3456}}; desolation; let death seize (from the margin).
from {{h7760}} and {{h410}}; God will place; Jesimael, an Israelite; Jesimael.
from {{h3456}}; desolate; Jishma, an Israelite; Ishma.
a primitive root; to lie waste; be desolate.
a primitive root; to place; intransitively, to be placed; be put (set).
from {{h3453}}; aged; Jeshishai, an Israelite; Jeshishai.
feminine passive participle of {{h3467}}; something saved, i.e. (abstractly) deliverance; hence, aid, victory, prosperity; deliverance, health, help(-ing), salvation, save, saving (health), welfare.
from an unused root meaning to gape (as the empty stomach); hunger; casting down.
from {{h7831}}; he will laugh; Jischak, the heir of Abraham; Isaac. Compare {{h3327}}.
a primitive root; to extend; hold out.
from {{h7737}}; level; Jishvi, the name of two Israelites; Ishuai, Ishvi, Isui, Jesui.
patronymically from {{h3440}}; a Jishvite (collectively) or descendants of Jishvi; Jesuites.
for {{h3091}}; he will save; Jeshua, the name of ten Israelites, also of a place in Palestine; Jeshua.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3442}}; Jeshua.
by Aramaic אִישַׁי; from the same as {{h3426}}; extant; Jishai, David's father; Jesse.
or יִשִּׁיָּהוּ; from {{h5383}} and {{h3050}}; Jah will lend; Jishshijah, the name of five Israelites; Ishiah, Isshiah, Ishijah, Jesiah.
from {{h7623}}; he will praise; Jishbach, an Israelite; Ishbah.
from {{h3427}} and {{h5011}}, with a pronominal suffix and a preposition interposed; his dwelling (is) in Nob; Jishbo-be-Nob, a Philistine; Ishbi-benob (from the margin).

from {{h7725}} and {{h3899}}; returner of bread; Jashubi-Lechem, an Israelite; Jashubi-lehem. (Prob. the text should be pointed יֹשְׁבֵי לֶחֶם and rendered '(they were) inhabitants of Lechem,' i.e. of Bethlehem (by contraction). Compare {{h3902}}).
patronymically from {{h3437}}; a Jashubite, or descendant of Jashub; Jashubites.
from an unused root corresponding to {{h7662}}; he will leave; Jishbak, a son of Abraham; Ishbak.
from {{h7725}} and {{h5971}}; people will return; Jashobam, the name of two or three Israelites; Jashobeam.
or יָשִׁיב; from {{h7725}}; he will return; Jashub, the name of two Israelites; Jashub.
from {{h3427}} and {{h7186}}; a hard seat; Joshbekashah, an Israelite; Joshbekashah.
from the same as {{h3445}} and {{h3050}}; Jah will empty; Jeshochajah, an Israelite; Jeshoaiah.
from {{h7737}}; he will level; Jishvah, an Israelite; Ishvah, Isvah.
from the same as {{h3418}}; yellowishness; greenish, yellow.

or יָרֵשׁ; a primitive root; to occupy (by driving out previous tenants, and possessing in their place); by implication, to seize, to rob, to inherit; also to expel, to impoverish, to ruin; cast out, consume, destroy, disinherit, dispossess, drive(-ing) out, enjoy, expel, × without fail, (give to, leave for) inherit(-ance, -or)   magistrate, be (make) poor, come to poverty, (give to, make to) possess, get (have) in (take) possession, seize upon, succeed, × utterly.
from {{h3418}}; paleness, whether of persons (from fright), or of plants (from drought); greenish, yellow.
from {{h7324}} and {{h5971}}; people will be poured forth; Jorkeam, a place in Palestine; Jorkeam.

perhaps from an unused root meaning to stand out, or exist; entity; used adverbially or as a copula for the substantive verb ({{h1961}}); there is or are (or any other form of the verb to be, as may suit the connection); (there) are, (he, it, shall, there, there may, there shall, there should) be, thou do, had, hast, (which) hath, (I, shalt, that) have, (he, it, there) is, substance, it (there) was, (there) were, ye will, thou wilt, wouldest.

a primitive root; properly, to sit down (specifically as judge. in ambush, in quiet); by implication, to dwell, to remain; causatively, to settle, to marry; (make to) abide(-ing), continue, (cause to, make to) dwell(-ing), ease self, endure, establish, × fail, habitation, haunt, (make to) inhabit(-ant), make to keep (house), lurking, × marry(-ing), (bring again to) place, remain, return, seat, set(-tle), (down-) sit(-down, still, -ting down, -ting (place) -uate), take, tarry.
from {{h3423}}; occupancy; possession.
from {{h3423}}; something occupied; a conquest; also a patrimony; heritage, inheritance, possession.
from {{h3427}} and {{h1}}; seat of (his) father; Jeshebab, an Israelite; Jeshebeab.
from the active participle of {{h3427}} and {{h7674}}, with a preposition and the article interposed; sitting in the seat; Joshebbash-Shebeth, an Israelite; that sat in the seat.
from the same as {{h3418}}; properly, green; concretely, a vegetable; green, herbs.

from {{h3417}} (in the sense of vacuity of color); properly, pallor, i.e. hence, the yellowish green of young and sickly vegetation; concretely, verdure, i.e. grass or vegetation; grass, green (thing).
a primitive root; to spit; × but, spit.
from {{h7495}} and {{h410}}; God will heal; Jirpeel, a place in Palestine; Irpeel.
a primitive root; properly, to be broken up (with any violent action) i.e. (figuratively) to fear; be grevious (only Isaiah 15:4; the rest belong to {{h7489}}).
or יִרְמְיָהוּ; from {{h7311}} and {{h3050}}; Jah will rise; Jirmejah, the name of eight or nine Israelites; Jeremiah.
from {{h7311}}; elevated; Jeremai, an Israelite; Jeremai.
from {{h7311}}; elevation; Jarmuth, the name of two places in Palestine; Jarmuth.
feminine of {{h3409}}; properly, the flank; but used only figuratively, the rear or recess; border, coast, part, quarter, side.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3411}}; a thigh; thigh.
from the same as {{h8577}}; extensive; Jithnan, a place in Palestine; Ithnan.
from an unused root meaning to endure, and {{h410}}; continued of God; Jathniel, an Israelite; Jathniel.
from the same as {{h3490}}; orphanage; Jithmah, an Israelite; Ithmah.
probably from {{h8518}}; it will hang, i.e. be high; Jithlah, a place in Palestine; Jethlah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3492}}; preeminent; as an adverb, very; exceeding(-ly), excellent.
from {{h3498}}; redundant; Jattir, a place in Palestine; Jattir.
passive participle of {{h3498}}; properly, what is left, i.e. (by implication) a gleaning; range.
from an unused root meaning to be lonely; a bereaved person; fatherless (child), orphan.

from {{h3498}}; properly, an overhanging, i.e. (by implication) an excess, superiority, remainder; also a small rope (as hanging free); abundant, cord, exceeding, excellancy(-ent), what they leave, that hath left, plentifully, remnant, residue, rest, string, with.

a primitive root; to jut over or exceed; by implication, to excel; (intransitively) to remain or be left; causatively to leave, cause to abound, preserve; excel, leave (a remnant), left behind, too much, make plenteous, preserve, (be, let) remain(-der, -ing, -nant), reserve, residue, rest.
plural of {{h3407}}; curtains; Jerioth, an Israelitess; Jerioth.
from an unused root meaning to be soft; the thigh (from its fleshy softness); by euphemistically the generative parts; figuratively, a shank, flank, side; × body, loins, shaft, side, thigh.
from {{h7378}}; literally he will contend; properly, adjective contentious; used as noun, an adversary; that content(-eth), that strive.
the same as {{h3401}}; Jarib, the name of three Israelites; Jarib.
from {{h3401}}; contentious; Jeribai, an Israelite; Jeribai.
or יְרִיָּהוּ; from {{h3384}} and {{h3050}}; Jah will throw; Jerijah, an Israelite; Jeriah, Jerijah.
or יְרֵחוֹ; or variation (1 Kings 16:34) יְרִיחֹה; perhaps from {{h3394}}; its month; or else from {{h7306}}; fragrant; Jericho or Jerecho, a place in Palestine; Jericho.
or יְרֵימוֹת; or יְרֵמוֹת; feminine plural from {{h7311}}; elevations; Jerimoth or Jeremoth, the name of twelve Israelites; Jermoth, Jerimoth, and Ramoth (from the margin).
from {{h3415}}; a hanging (as tremulous); curtain.
by variation from {{h3477}} and {{h410}} with directive enclitic; right towards God; Jesarelah, an Israelite; Jesharelah.
patronymically from {{h3478}}; a Jisreelite or descendant of Jisrael; of Israel, Israelite.
feminine of {{h3481}}; a Jisreelitess or female descendant of Jisrael; Israelitish.
feminine of {{h3477}}; rectitude; uprightness.
from {{h3474}}; upright; Jeshurun, a symbolic name for Israel; Jeshurun.
(strictly yis-saws-kawr'); from {{h5375}} and {{h7939}}; he will bring a reward; Jissaskar, a son of Jacob; Issachar.
from an unused root meaning to blanch; gray-haired, i.e. an aged man; stoop for age.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h853}}; a sign of the object of a verb; whom.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3427}}; to sit or dwell; dwell, (be) set, sit.
from an unused root meaning to pin through or fast; a peg; nail, paddle, pin, stake.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3478}}; Israel.
from {{h8280}} and {{h410}}; he will rule as God; Jisraël, a symbolical name of Jacob; also (typically) of his posterity; Israel.
from {{h3474}}; the right; Jesher, an Israelite; Jesher.

a primitive root; to be straight or even; figuratively, to be (causatively, to make) right, pleasant, prosperous; direct, fit, seem good (meet),   please (will), be (esteem, go) right (on), bring (look, make, take the) straight (way), be upright(-ly).
from {{h3474}}; straight (literally or figuratively); convenient, equity, Jasher, just, meet(-est),   pleased well right(-eous), straight, (most) upright(-ly, -ness).
from {{h3474}}; the right; equity, meet, right, upright(-ness).
from an unused root meaning to polish; a gem supposed to be jasper (from the resemblance in name); jasper.
or יְשַׁעְיָהוּ; from {{h3467}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has saved; Jeshajah, the name of seven Israelites; Isaiah, Jesaiah, Jeshaiah.
probably from the same as {{h8227}}; he will hide; Jishpan, an Israelite; Ishpan.
perhaps from {{h8192}}; he will scratch; Jishpah, an Israelite; Ispah.
the same as {{h3499}}; Jether, the name of five or six Israelites and of one Midianite; Jether, Jethro. Compare {{h3503}}.
or יֵשַׁע; from {{h3467}}; liberty, deliverance, prosperity; safety, salvation, saving.
from {{h3467}}; saving; Jishi, the name of four Israelites; Ishi.
feminine of {{h3465}}; Jeshanah, a place in Palestine; Jeshanah.

a primitive root; properly, to be open, wide or free, i.e. (by implication) to be safe; causatively, to free or succor; × at all, avenging, defend, deliver(-er), help, preserve, rescue, be safe, bring (having) salvation, save(-iour), get victory.
the same as {{h3463}}; Jashen, an Israelite; Jashen.
from {{h3462}}; old; old.
a primitive root; properly, to be slack or languid, i.e. (by implication) sleep (figuratively, to die); also to grow old, stale or inveterate; old (store), remain long, (make to) sleep.
from {{h3462}}; sleepy; asleep, (one out of) sleep(-eth, -ing), slept.
or יִשְׁמַעְיָהוּlemma יְשְׁמַעְיָהוּ first vowel, corrected to יִשְׁמַעְיָהוּ; from {{h8085}} and {{h3050}}; Jah will hear; Jishmajah, the name of two Israelites; Ishmaiah.
from {{h8104}}; preservative; Jishmerai, an Israelite; Ishmerai.
